## Step 4
To find $P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453)$, we need to standardize the values 52.761 and 54.453 to z-scores using the formula $z = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu}{\sigma / \sqrt{n}}$.

## Step 5
Calculate the z-score for $\bar{X} = 52.761$. $z = \frac{52.761 - 54.030}{0.846} = \frac{-1.269}{0.846} = -1.5$.

