## Step 7
Using a standard normal distribution table or calculator, find $P(-1.5 \leq Z \leq 0.5)$, where $Z$ is a standard normal variable.

## Step 8
$P(-1.5 \leq Z \leq 0.5) = P(Z \leq 0.5) - P(Z \leq -1.5)$. Using a standard normal distribution table: $P(Z \leq 0.5) = 0.6915$ and $P(Z \leq -1.5) = 0.0668$.

